diagnoses.name: Sjögren's Syndrome
diagnoses.description: An autoimmune disease that affects the glands responsible for keeping the eyes, mouth, and other parts of the body moist and lubricated, potentially explaining the combination of irritated eyes and periodontal disease.

diagnoses.name: Granulomatosis with Polyangiitis
diagnoses.description: A rare disease causing inflammation of the blood vessels (vasculitis), which can affect the eyes, mouth, and other organs, potentially leading to symptoms like those described.

diagnoses.name: Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE)
diagnoses.description: A chronic autoimmune disease that can affect any part of the body, including the eyes, mouth, and immune system, potentially causing a wide range of symptoms.

diagnoses.name: Common Variable Immune Deficiency (CVID)
diagnoses.description: A disorder characterized by decreased levels of several immunoglobulin classes, leading to an increased susceptibility to infections, which might indirectly affect oral health and potentially cause other symptoms.

diagnoses.name: Rheumatoid Arthritis
diagnoses.description: An autoimmune disease that can cause a wide range of systemic symptoms, including effects on the eyes and oral health.

diagnoses.name: Behçet's Disease
diagnoses.description: A rare disorder causing blood vessel inflammation throughout the body, which could explain some of the symptoms, including eye irritation and possibly oral health issues.

diagnoses.name: Hereditary Hemorrhagic Telangiectasia (HHT)
diagnoses.description: A genetic disorder that leads to the development of abnormal blood vessels, similar to arteriovenous malformations.

diagnoses.name: HIV/AIDS
diagnoses.description: The virus can cause a wide range of symptoms, including decreased immunoglobulin levels, periodontal disease due to opportunistic infections, and systemic symptoms that might explain frequent waking.

diagnoses.name: Primary Immunodeficiency Disorders
diagnoses.description: A group of disorders characterized by defects in the body's immune defenses, leading to recurrent infections, potentially affecting oral health and causing a wide range of symptoms.

diagnoses.name: Chronic Fatigue Syndrome
diagnoses.description: A complex disorder characterized by extreme fatigue that can worsen with physical or mental activity but doesn't improve with rest. While it doesn't directly cause the other symptoms, it can be associated with immune system problems.

diagnoses: Blepharospasm as a component of a neurologic disorder (e.g., Parkinson's disease, Dystonia)

Sarcoidosis with lung involvement but normal pulmonary function tests in early stages
Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), with a differential diagnosis of asthma-COPD overlap syndrome
Systemic lupus erythematosus (as a less common cause with differential diagnosis)

diagnoses.name: Diabetes Mellitus
diagnoses.description: A group of diseases that result in too much sugar in the blood (high blood glucose).

diagnoses.name: Rheumatoid Arthritis
diagnoses.description: A chronic inflammatory disorder affecting many joints, including those in the hands and feet.

diagnoses.name: Hereditary Hemorrhagic Telangiectasia
diagnoses.description: A genetic disorder that leads to abnormal blood vessel formation.

diagnoses.name: Stress Cardiomyopathy (Takotsubo Cardiomyopathy)
diagnoses.description: A temporary heart condition that's often brought on by stressful situations and can mimic a heart attack.

diagnoses.name: Chronic Sinusitis
diagnoses.description: A common condition in which the cavities around nasal passages (sinuses) become inflamed and swollen for at least 12 weeks, despite treatment attempts.

diagnoses.name: Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS)
diagnoses.description: A hormonal disorder common among women of reproductive age.

diagnoses.name: Osteoarthritis
diagnoses.description: A type of arthritis that occurs when flexible tissue at the ends of bones wears down.

diagnoses.name: Hypertension
diagnoses.description: A condition in which the force of the blood against the artery walls is too high.

diagnoses.name: Metabolic Syndrome
diagnoses.description: A cluster of conditions that occur together, increasing your risk of heart disease, stroke, and type 2 diabetes.

diagnoses.name: Gout
diagnoses.description: A form of arthritis characterized by severe pain, redness, and tenderness in joints.

diagnoses: Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) due to environmental exposure

diagnoses.name: Anaphylaxis
diagnoses.description: A severe, life-threatening allergic reaction that can occur suddenly after exposure to an allergen. Symptoms can include abdominal pain, fainting (syncope), swelling (angioedema), eye redness (conjunctival injection), and hives.

diagnoses.name: Hereditary Angioedema
diagnoses.description: A rare genetic condition causing episodes of severe swelling (angioedema) in various parts of the body, including the abdomen, face, and limbs. It may also present with abdominal cramps and, less commonly, hives or conjunctival injections.

diagnoses.name: Acute Urticaria
diagnoses.description: An outbreak of hives or welts on the skin, which can be triggered by an allergen. It may also cause swelling, abdominal pain, and sometimes syncope due to a severe allergic reaction.

diagnoses.name: Mastocytosis
diagnoses.description: A disorder characterized by an excessive number of mast cells in the body. Symptoms can include hives, syncope, abdominal cramps, angioedema, and redness in the eyes.

diagnoses.name: Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE)
diagnoses.description: An autoimmune disease that can cause a wide variety of symptoms, including conjunctival injection, abdominal pain, skin rash, and in rare cases, angioedema and syncope.

diagnoses.name: Carcinoid Syndrome
diagnoses.description: A symptom complex caused by carcinoid tumors. It can present with flushing, diarrhea, abdominal cramps, conjunctival injection, and rarely, hives or angioedema.

diagnoses.name: Food Allergy
diagnoses.description: An adverse immune response to a food protein. Symptoms can include hives, abdominal cramps, syncope, conjunctival injection, and angioedema.

diagnoses.name: Toxic Shock Syndrome
diagnoses.description: A rare, life-threatening complication of certain bacterial infections. It is characterized by sudden high fever, rash, vomiting, diarrhea, muscle aches, syncope, and in some cases, hives and angioedema.

diagnoses.name: Alpha-gal Syndrome
diagnoses.description: An allergy to red meat and other products made from mammals, which is caused by a tick bite. Symptoms can include hives, abdominal pain, nausea, and in some cases, anaphylaxis.

diagnoses.name: Drug Allergy
diagnoses.description: An immune system reaction to a medication. Symptoms can range from mild, such as hives and angioedema, to severe, including syncope, abdominal pain, and anaphylaxis.

diagnoses: Inflammatory bowel disease (Crohn's disease and ulcerative colitis)
Demyelinating diseases of the central nervous system

diagnoses.name: Migraine with Aura
diagnoses.description: A type of headache that is accompanied by visual disturbances (scintillating scotoma), sensory symptoms, or speech disturbances (aphasia). Nausea, vomiting, and sensitivity to light and sound are common.

diagnoses.name: Transient Ischemic Attack (TIA)
diagnoses.description: Often called a mini-stroke, a TIA may cause sudden headache, difficulty speaking or understanding speech (aphasia), and visual disturbances, without causing permanent damage.

diagnoses.name: Meningitis
diagnoses.description: Infection of the protective membranes covering the brain and spinal cord. Symptoms include severe headache, nausea, sensitivity to light, and altered mental status.

diagnoses.name: Acoustic Neuroma
diagnoses.description: A benign tumor on the nerve that connects the ear to the brain, leading to hearing loss, tinnitus, and balance disorders. Headache and nausea might occur secondary to increased intracranial pressure.

diagnoses.name: Stroke
diagnoses.description: A condition where blood supply to part of the brain is interrupted or reduced, preventing brain tissue from getting oxygen and nutrients. Symptoms include headache, trouble speaking (aphasia), and visual disturbances.

diagnoses.name: Brain Tumor
diagnoses.description: An abnormal growth of cells within the brain that can cause headaches, nausea, speech difficulties (aphasia), and hearing loss, among other symptoms.

diagnoses.name: Multiple Sclerosis
diagnoses.description: An autoimmune disease affecting the brain and spinal cord, causing a variety of neurological symptoms, including visual problems, balance and coordination issues, and in some cases, headache and nausea.

diagnoses.name: Vestibular Migraine
diagnoses.description: A variant of migraine where vertigo, dizziness, or imbalance occurs, often accompanied by typical migraine symptoms like headache, visual disturbances, and nausea.

diagnoses.name: Temporal Arteritis
diagnoses.description: An inflammation of blood vessels, typically in the head, causing severe headaches, scalp tenderness, vision problems, and sometimes symptoms similar to stroke, including speech difficulties.

diagnoses.name: Posterior Circulation Stroke
diagnoses.description: A stroke affecting the back part of the brain, which can lead to vision problems, difficulty speaking (aphasia), imbalance, nausea, and headache.
